Welcome!
Southwestern Electric Cooperative provides power to nearly 23,000 residential, commercial, agricultural, and industrial members in southwestern Illinois, including parts of the St. Louis Metro East. As a not-for-profit utility, Southwestern Electric is committed to providing high-quality energy services at the lowest possible prices. We're guided by the simple belief that a member-owned, member-controlled company should operate in the best interests of the families, neighbors and communities it serves.



Recent Articles



Crews Working to Restore Few Remaining Outages 
Monday, July 24, 2017
Southwestern line crews have restored power to all but six of the remaining members.


116 Members Remain Without Power
Monday, July 24, 2017
As of 7:30 a.m., Southwestern Electric crews are working to restore power the remaining 116 members without power.


Members Asked To Prepare For Overnight Outages
Sunday, July 23, 2017
Southwestern Electric crews continue to make progress restoring service this evening after today’s storm interrupted power to 3,300 cooperative members. At 11:30 p.m., about 400 members remained without power.









Co-op Reminders



Aug 25-Sept 8
Absentee voting available at the co-op’s headquarters (525 US Route 40 in Greenville), Monday-Friday, 8 a.m.-4:30 p.m.; Saturday, Sept. 2, 10 a.m.-12 p.m. 



 
Sept 9
79th Annual Meeting of Members at Greenville Jr. High School, St. Jacob and St. Elmo facilities. Voting 7 a.m. - 10 a.m.
Try Our New App!
Pay your bill, sign up for alerts and reminders, view your daily, weekly or monthly energy usage, and send and receive outage information with SWEC IL , our mobile app for your smart phone or tablet. Now available on the App Store   and on Google Play.
 










  
















