Home / Community / Our Giving / Community Connections Report / Contributions by Operating Company / Southwestern Electric Power Company / Texas 





Texas Contributions




Southwestern Electric Power Company Contributions
Dear SWEPCO Communities:

For more than 100 years, SWEPCO has provided affordable and reliable electric service to communities in Arkansas, Louisiana or Texas. One way we show our appreciation for customers is through community service and partnerships. 

In 2016, SWEPCO investors and shareholders supported hundreds of organizations, agencies and causes. Whether it was helping food banks feed the hungry, providing scholarships for local students, or bringing the performing arts to families, SWEPCO was proud to contribute financial support to organizations that are doing incredible work.

This report includes a list of some of the agencies that received contributions from SWEPCO and the American Electric Power Foundation. 

The East Texas Food Bank was one of our beneficiaries last year. With the help of 200 partner agencies, it works to reach the more than 25 percent of East Texas children who are at risk of going hungry. This food bank serves more than 250,000 people in 26 counties. And, in Fiscal Year 2016, it served more than 21.8 million meals. 

Agencies and non-profits like the East Texas Food Bank do so much to help our citizens. At SWEPCO, supporting the neighborhoods and communities where we live and work are a top priority. We may be a power company, but our true power in our communities comes from our people.


            Sincerely,

            Venita McCellon-Allen
            President and COO
        
Texas Contributions






